it den Methoden der Gesprächsanalyse untersucht, wie Besucherinnen und Besucher das Kommunikationsangebot im Ausstellungsraum für die interaktive Konstruktion von Wissen nutzen. Analysiert wird speziell, wie sie mit ihrer Interaktion an das multimodale Kommunikationsangebot im Ausstellungsraum anknüpfen. Das erlaubt schließlich, die beiden analytischen Zugänge in einen übergeordneten theoretischen Rahmen zu integrieren.  aThis study investigates museum exhibitions as multimodal communication offerings, of which texts and exhibits are just as much a part as exhibition architecture and design. It reconstructs the communicative potential of exhibitions from a text-linguistic and semiotic perspective before using conversation analysis to examine how visitors use exhibitions to construct knowledge about the exhibition topic.  aIssued also in print.  afunded by Schweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aBesucherforschung. 4aInteraktion. 4aMulitmodalität. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / German.2bisacsh  aInteraction.  aMultimodality.  aVisitor Research.2 aSchweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1z97831107507060 cEPUBz97831105734040 cprintz978311057290240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110572933zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110572933zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110572933/original  a978-3-11-075070-6 DG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA